OL,7,F"Drivers and teams knew they could
OL,8,Fcount on him, his timing was
OL,9,Fmeticulous, his notes delivered with
OL,10,Funshakeable calm, and his attention to
OL,11,Fdetail was second to none.
OL,13,F"But beyond the stages, it was Dai's
OL,14,Fcharacter that made him special. He
OL,15,Fwas gentle, humble, and unfailingly
OL,16,Fgenerous with his time, whether
OL,17,Fhelping a newcomer find their feet or
OL,18,Fchecking in quietly on a teammate
OL,19,Fafter a tough day. To many, he was the
OL,20,Fsoul of a service park: never loud,
OL,21,Fbut always present when it mattered.
